text: A septum (Latin: something that encloses; plural Septa) is a partition separating two cavities or spaces. Examples include: *Nasal Septum: the cartilage wall separating the nostrils of the human nose.Often deviated or perforated through physical injury or cocaine abuse. *Cephalopod Septa: walls between each chamber, or siphuncle, in shells of nautiloids, ammonites, and belemnites; i.e. cephalopods that retain an external shell. *The wall dividing the right side of the heart from the left side. Fungi produce septa to partition filamentous hyphae into discrete cells. Category:Anatomy
title: Septum
